<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-25T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/9–2551: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States</hi> (<gloss target="#t_GATT1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">GATT</hi></gloss>) <hi rend="italic">Delegation</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d597fn1">Repeated to Rome as
                                1394.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-25T19:00:00-04:00">September
                                    25, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Gatt 39. For Thorp. Today Secy spoke Gasperi<note n="2" xml:id="d597fn2">Italian Prime Minister Alcide De Gasperi was engaged in talks with
                                the United States Government at this time in Washington, following a
                                session of the North Atlantic Council in Ottawa, Canada; for
                                documentation on these meetings, see <ref target="frus1951v04p1">volume IV</ref>.</note> re <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> vote on Czech issue. Gasperi promised consider
                            carefully but stated he uninformed. Suggest you inform Ital deleg and
                            request he inquire for affirmative decision.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>